  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Self financially sustainable business through sunflower production and processing of cooking oil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Petauke District Farmers Association was legally registered in 2004 with a membership of about 500 farmers and overtime has shown growth in its membership to 6 000 individual farmers. However  only about 500 members had renewed their membership in 2017.The association covers the whole district in terms of its operation with 150 Information Centers. Each information centre pays an affiliation fee for it to actively participate in the affairs of the association. The greatest benefit of members in the association is capacity building and Market for sunflower. The association has trained 450 members in poultry management through the poultry business matching grant awarded by the Zambian government through the Ministry of Agriculture. They have also conducted trainings in bee keeping.The association provides Lima credit scheme to members where members pay 50% to the association and the last 50% after harvest. The association makes ZMW 100 per hectare as facilitation fee of the Lima Credit Scheme. As part of the sustainability strategy  the association decided to develop and submit a concept to United States Development of Africa &#x2013; USADF to process cooking oil from sunflower which they have been funded.The association has been running this business for over a year and have since managed by acquire its own land and built processing plant and office premises.The project will focus on improving the marketing of the product and financial management. It will also involve the lead farmers since they are the backbone to increased purchase of raw material and this will be done by holding a sustainable service workshop with the association in order for them to improve on their extension services to their members and increase member commitment and revenue which may lead to financial sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The desire of the association is to diverse their income sources as a way of increasing their capital base and reducing on donor dependency. The association also realizes the need to increase its membership base as it has an impact on their revenue  however the association sees the need to provide more membership services to its members as a way of proving its relevance need for members to affiliate. The association also sees the need to improve on accountability and business planning.
     BHAG 2019:To become self sustainable through crop  Livestock diversification  Improve sunflower out grower scheme and increase membership base by 333 monthly as a way of increasing their capital base and reducing on donor dependency.
      BHAG 2022: To increase membership base to 10 000-20 000 as it has an impact on      the association revenue.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">They project will focus on marketing  member involvement and financial management</narrative>
  </description>
